Package: margot.sim
Type: Package
Title: Simulate Longitudinal Data with Masking and Monte Carlo Evaluation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Joseph", "Bulbulia", email = "joseph.bulbulia@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5861-2056"))
Author: Joseph Bulbulia [aut, cre] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5861-2056>)
Description: Extensions to the margot package for simulating longitudinal data 
    using Structural Causal Models (SCMs). Provides sophisticated capabilities 
    for applying various masks (censoring, measurement error, selection bias) 
    to simulated data, running Monte Carlo simulations to evaluate statistical 
    estimators, supporting flexible non-normal distributions, and creating a 
    unified framework for causal inference method evaluation.
